### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

Don't known / other

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

Firefox shows a warning `unreachable code after return statement`. This warning is not visisble in Chrome.

The warning disappears when `optimization: false` is set in the `angular.json`

The reproducible example is based on the [Hello World example of Angular Playground](https://angular.dev/playground). The only change I made is removing `"optimization": false,` under `development` in the `angular.json` and the warning appears in the console.

When inspecting the warning in the reproducible example it shows up in:
```
checkNoChanges() {
    if (!ngDevMode) return;
    try {
      this.exhaustive ??= this._lView[INJECTOR].get(UseExhaustiveCheckNoChanges, USE_EXHAUSTIVE_CHECK_NO_CHANGES_DEFAULT);
    } catch {
      this.exhaustive = USE_EXHAUSTIVE_CHECK_NO_CHANGES_DEFAULT;
    }
    checkNoChangesInternal(this._lView, this.exhaustive);
  }
```

In our production code, it shows up in:
```
checkNoChanges() {
            return;
            try {
              this.exhaustive ??= this._lView[n_].get(RUe, Xde)
            } catch {
              this.exhaustive = Xde
            }
          }
```

In this last function, there is a return statement at the beginning of the function.
The issue seems to be introduced when we updated to angular 20 as far as I can remember

